  <!-- EN: conditionall -->
  <PS_ReconPodConditionallResearch.label>条件</PS_ReconPodConditionallResearch.label>
  <!-- EN: Due to it’s bulk and power requirements, the reconditioning pod proved infeasible for use in transit. A more portable option was required for those who underwent conditioning. From this necessity plasteel researchers developed Conditionall. A pill containing high concentrations of the same neural transmitter manipulating chemicals used in the reconditioning pod. One dose has half the effect as one hour in a pod. Ideal for those who are traveling, bedridden, or otherwise unable to reach a pod. -->
  <PS_ReconPodConditionallResearch.description>由于其体积和电力要求，修整舱被证明不适合在运输途中使用。我们需要一种更便携的选择，以方便那些接受调理的人。根据这一需要，Plasteel 公司的研究人员开发出了 Conditionall。这种药丸含有高浓度的神经递质操纵化学物质，与调节舱中使用的化学物质相同。一剂药的效果是在吊舱中一小时效果的一半。非常适合旅行、卧病在床或无法进入吊舱的人。</PS_ReconPodConditionallResearch.description>
  <!-- EN: neural cement -->
  <PS_ReconPodNeuralCementResearch.label>神经水泥</PS_ReconPodNeuralCementResearch.label>
  <!-- EN: Due to growing complaints from investors, involving conditioning failure related riots, researches were tasked with developing a way to make conditioning perminate. The result, Neural Cementing. A highly aggressive procedure that involves application of a plasteel based neural cement. This substance has the ability to permanently apply the effects of conditioning, without the need for maintenance.\n\nThe procedure does have drawbacks. Firstly it is very risky with a high rate of failure resulting in brain damage or death. Thus, should only be performed by skilled surgeons working in an ideal environment. Secondly, the cementing process, locks in neural pathways, preventing any future conditioning. -->
  <PS_ReconPodNeuralCementResearch.description>由于投资者的抱怨越来越多，涉及到与调节失败有关的暴乱，研究人员被委以开发一种使调节永久化的方法的重任。这就是 "神经固化"。这是一种极具侵略性的程序，包括使用一种以塑料为基础的神经水泥。这种物质具有永久性的调节效果，无需维护。

这种手术也有缺点。首先，它非常危险，失败率很高，会导致脑损伤或死亡。因此，只有技术娴熟的外科医生才能在理想的环境中工作。其次，粘合过程会锁住神经通路，阻碍今后的调节。</PS_ReconPodNeuralCementResearch.description>
  <!-- EN: reconditioning pod -->
  <PS_ReconPodResearch.label>修复舱</PS_ReconPodResearch.label>
  <!-- EN: Further advances in plasteel study have resulted in new alteration technology. This time not in the body, but in the mind. Though the combination of neural transmitter manipulation, suggestive stimulus, and a digital psychologist AI, scientist have found a way to change the core components of a patient's personality. Obsessions with dangerous elements like fire or drugs can be removed, or a poor work ethic can be swapped out for a more industrious personality.\n\nUnfortunately the conditioning is not permanent. Without proper maintenance the patients psyche will become aware of and reject the foreign changes. As conditioning weakens the patient’s mind will grow more unstable. Eventually resulting in a  mental breakdown and reversion to their per-conditioning state. To avoid this it is recommended that all reconditioned subjects return to their pods for one hour every two days. -->
  <PS_ReconPodResearch.description>塑钢研究的进一步发展带来了新的改造技术。这次不是在身体上，而是在心灵上。通过神经发射器操纵、暗示性刺激和数字心理学家人工智能的结合，科学家们找到了改变病人性格核心成分的方法。对火或毒品等危险元素的迷恋可以被消除，或者将不良的职业道德换成更勤奋的个性。

遗憾的是，这种调节并非永久性的。如果没有适当的维护，病人的心理就会意识到并拒绝外来的改变。随着调节作用的减弱，病人的心理会越来越不稳定。最终导致精神崩溃，恢复到调理前的状态。为避免出现这种情况，建议所有经过调理的受试者每两天回到他们的舱内一小时。</PS_ReconPodResearch.description>
